"Molnár A.","Catalytic applications of amorphous alloys: Expectations, achievements, and disappointments",2011,"Applied Surface Science","257","19",,"8151","8164",,,10.1016/j.apsusc.2010.12.046,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-79958856140&partnerID=40&md5=432a3e24c7086f8369bd290744df1e70","Department of Organic Chemistry, University of Szeged, Dóm tér 8, H-6720 Szeged, Hungary","Molnár, A., Department of Organic Chemistry, University of Szeged, Dóm tér 8, H-6720 Szeged, Hungary","This review intends to summarize the major achievements in the application of amorphous alloys as precursors of catalyst materials. This non-traditional catalyst preparation method may provide supported catalysts with novel chemical and structural properties. Selected examples for both glassy alloy precursors and those fabricated by mechanochemistry include CO oxidation over binary and ternary alloys, dehydrogenation over Cu-M (M = Ti, Zr or Hf), one-step synthesis of methyl isobutyl ketone, and selective hydrogenation of unsaturated carbonyl compounds. Ni alloys for methanation developed for the project to solve global warming by recycling carbon dioxide are also discussed. © 2010 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.","Amorphous alloys; Catalytic applications; Crystallization; Dehydrogenation; Electrocatalysis; Hydrogenation","Catalyst material; Catalyst preparation; Catalytic applications; CO oxidation; Glassy alloys; Mechano-chemistry; Methyl isobutyl ketone; Ni alloys; Non-traditional; One step synthesis; Selected examples; Selective hydrogenation; Unsaturated carbonyl compounds; Amorphous materials; Binary alloys; Carbon dioxide; Carbonylation; Catalysts; Copper alloys; Dehydrogenation; Electrocatalysis; Global warming; Hafnium; Hydrogenation; Ketones; Unsaturated compounds; Zirconium; Amorphous alloys",,,,,,"Klement Jr., W., Willens, R.H., Duwez, P., (1960) Nature (London), 187, pp. 869-870; Duwez, P., Willens, R.H., Klement Jr., W., (1960) J. Appl. Phys., 31, pp. 1136-1137; Duwez, P., (1967) Trans. Am. Soc. Met., 60, p. 607; Molnár, Á., Smith, G.V., Bartók, M., (1989) Adv. Catal., 36, pp. 329-383; Baiker, A., (1989) Faraday Discuss. Chem. Soc., 87, pp. 239-251; Baiker, A., (1993) Metallic Glasses III, p. 121; Baiker, A., Metallic glasses (1997) Handbook of Heterogeneous Catalysis, 3, pp. 803-814; Baiker, A., Molnár, Á., Metallic glasses (2008) Handbook of Heterogeneous Catalysis, 3, pp. 1285-1298. , 2nd ed. G. Ertl, H. Knözinger, F. Schüth, J. Weitkamp, Wiley-VCH Weinheim; Suryanarayana, C., (2001) Prog. Mater. Sci., 46, pp. 1-184; Baiker, A., Gasser, D., Lenzner, J., Reller, A., Schlögl, R., (1990) J. Catal., 126, pp. 555-571; Schlögl, R., Loose, G., Wesemann, M., Baiker, A., (1992) J. Catal., 137, pp. 139-157; Baiker, A., Tagliaferri, S., MacIejewski, M., (1993) Ber. Bunsen Phys. Chem., 97, pp. 288-292; Gredig, S., Tagliaferri, S., Baiker, A., (1995) Stud. Surf. Sci. Catal., 96, pp. 285-295; Baiker, A., MacIejewski, M., Tagliaferri, S., Hug, P., (1995) J. Catal., 151, pp. 407-419; Katona, T., Hegedüs, Z., Kopasz, C., Molnár, Á., Bartók, M., (1990) Catal. Lett., 5, pp. 361-368; Molnár, Á., Katona, T., Bartók, M., Varga, K., (1991) J. Mol. Catal., 64, pp. 41-51; Domokos, L., Katona, T., Molnár, Á., Lovas, A., (1996) Appl. Catal. A, 142, pp. 151-158; Molnár, Á., Katona, T., Bartók, M., Perczel, I.V., Hegedüs, Z., Kopasz, Cs., (1991) Mater. Sci. Eng. A, 134, pp. 1083-1086; Katona, T., Molnár, Á., Perczel, I.V., Kopasz, C., Hegeds, Z., (1992) Surf. Interface Anal., 19, pp. 519-523; Martinek, T., Molnár, Á., Katona, T., Bartók, M., Lovas, A., (1996) J. Mol. Catal. A: Chem., 112, pp. 85-92; Katona, T., Molnár, Á., (1995) J. Catal., 153, pp. 333-343; Szummer, A., Janik-Czachor, M., Molnár, Á., Marchuk, I., Varga, M., Filipek, S.M., (2001) J. Mol. Catal. A: Chem., 176, pp. 205-212; Pisarek, M., Janik-Czachor, M., Gebert, A., Molnár, Á., Kedzierzawski, P., Rác, B., (2004) Appl. Catal. A, 267, pp. 1-8; Pisarek, M., Janik-Czachor, M., Mo